\nhighway.','Viñales','Viñales','Viñales','Viñales,Pinar del Rio,Cuba ','Viñales','Pinar del Rio','Cuba ','en'),(14,12,'Madurai','Madurai is one of the oldest cities of India, with a history dating all the way back to the Sangam period of the pre Christian era. The glory of Madurai returned in a diminished form in the earlier part of this millennium; it later on came under the rule of the Vijayanagar kingdom after its ransack by the ravaging armies of Delhi (Malik Kafur). During the 16th and 18th centuries, Madurai was ruled by the Nayak Emperors, the foremost of whom was Tirumalai Nayakar. The Sangam period poet Nakkeerar is associated with some of the Tiruvilayaadal episodes of Sundareswarar - that are enacted as a part of temple festival traditions even today.','Madurai is one of the oldest cities of India, with a history dating all the way back to the Sangam period of the pre Christian era. The glory of Madurai returned in a diminished form in the earlier part of this millennium; it later on came under the rule of the Vijayanagar kingdom after its ransack by the ravaging armies of Delhi (Malik Kafur). During the 16th and 18th centuries, Madurai was ruled by the Nayak Emperors, the foremost of whom was Tirumalai Nayakar. The Sangam period poet Nakkeerar is associated with some of the Tiruvilayaadal episodes of Sundareswarar - that are enacted as a part of temple festival traditions even today.','Madurai','Madurai','Madurai','Madurai,Tamil Nadu [Madris],India ','Madurai','Tamil Nadu [Madris]','India ','en'),(15,13,'Madurai1','adsf','asdf','Madurai1','','','Madurai1,Tamil Nadu [Madris],India ','Madurai1','Tamil Nadu [Madris]','India ','en'),(16,14,'TestRQIXTAUUKZBHCYXPOIEQTQRFNYCFSDRSGTVWQUMVHCLHSPRLEECBDIECEMUILZCNCBNQXLNQDYFJOOSSAFSYZZPHOWEWJZJUEVE','Test Description','Test Location Description','Test Meta','Test Meta Description','Test Meta Keyword','TestRQIXTAUUKZBHCYXPOIEQTQRFNYCFSDRSGTVWQUMVHCLHSPRLEECBDIECEMUILZCNCBNQXLNQDYFJOOSSAFSYZZPHOWEWJZJUEVE,Alabama,U