INSERT INTO `staticpage_content` VALUES (1,1,'Home','Home','Home','Home',NULL,'en'),(2,2,'Who we are?','Who we are?','Who we are?','Who we are?','<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;re the experts on Cuba! Our mission is to show you the REAL CUBA, the less travelled parts of the country which preserves Cuba&acute;s most genuine traditions. You will be able to discover the country&acute;s real heart and spirit. No need for a sea of foreign-owned resorts. My Trip to Cuba with VenaCuba is the right way to spend the best holidays ever and the most important thing is that the money you spend stays in Cuban hands (88$ every 100$ goes to locals)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our job is to connect travellers with all local property managers that will provide memorable accommodations and experiences to you, by offering a customized service that you won&acute;t forget. We are in charge of representing Cuban B&amp;B owners directly. This means we offer an extensive catalogue containing pictures, descriptions and reviews!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You will discover that Cuba is more than sand and sun. With VenaCuba you will have the adventure of your life and will discover people, places, and a unique culture that you won&rsquo;t find anywhere else.</p>\r\n<h2>Why to choose VenaCuba? </h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are the best choice to bridge the touristic gap created by the embargo. Many tourists come to Cuba and stay at spiritless foreign-owned resorts but we go far beyond that by offering you a REAL slice of the Cuban life. Booking with us means that you are supporting local and small businesses and communities. You will enjoy a deeper experience because you aren&rsquo;t just visiting Cuba &ndash; no - you&rsquo;re helping to make it a better place. Your money stays in Cuban hands not in the hands of any government or large company because 88$ every 100$ goes to the locals.</p>\r\n','en'),(3,3,'What do we do?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<div class=\"what-offer\">\r\n	<p>\r\n		We care about your Satisfaction. That´s our Business and Purpose</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		We personally know each B&B Owner and work with them because they are the best in their business.  However, even with the best preparation and arrangements, problems may arise.  You just need to contact US in case of any issues, questions, discrepancies or any dissatisfaction you may have. We will work and do our best to set it right. It is a fact that sometimes language barriers and cultural differences can encumber the act of communication. You don´t have to worry because we understand CUBANS and VISITORS as well, so it will be our pleasure to mediate any problems and ultimately provide you a refund where necessary.  Being involved in dispute resolution make us be prepared to use information to ensure that the B&B descriptions are accurate and updated so what you expect is exactly what you get in your trip to Cuba.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n','en'),(4,4,'What do we offer?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>An online calendar on Cuban B&B availability</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our uniqueness is that we offer an online calendar specialized in Cuban B&B availability making possible that our customers can book with confidence throughout the year. This is possible because we represent each property, so you don´t have to worry about having any overbooking problem. You just have to pay a deposit, usually a 20% or the full amount. You can use Visa, MasterCard or PayPal for payment.</p>\r\n','en'),(5,5,'Payment Policies','Payment Policies','Payment Policies','Payment Policies','<div class=\"row clearfix\">\r\n	<ul class=\"pay-ment\">\r\n		<li>\r\n			<strong>Deposits and Payment:</strong><br />\r\n			When sending your payment information you authorize us to make all the payment arrangements with the suppliers accordingly.</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			<strong>Cancellations and Changes:</strong><br />\r\n We will make sure – as your booking agent – that you receive notifications concerning any significant changes in your travel arrangements, but we accept no liability for any changes or costs incurred as result of this. According to the supplier’s terms and conditions, you can choose whether accepting the change to the arrangements or not. You can accept an alternative to your travel arrangements offered by the supplier. In case you want to cancel your arrangement you have the right to receive any applicable refund. \r\n </li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			<strong>What If I Cancel My Booking?</strong><br />\r\n			In case you decide to cancel your arrangements with us, you may be entitled to a full refund. All you need is to send the original voucher so any applicable refund can be considered. Please note that 30 days before the booking ->100% refund, less than 30Days 80% refund, and\r\nthe 20% will remain as a Lifetime Deposit.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n','en'),(6,6,'Terms & Conditions',NULL,NULL,NULL,'	<p>\r\n		The following terms and conditions contain and describe what you are legally entitled to expect from us when purchasing travel related services. You will also find your obligations as a customer.</p>\r\n	<h3>\r\n		<a id=\"h.58vh2wbxr1h8\" name=\"h.58vh2wbxr1h8\"></a>1. The Agreement With You</h3>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Products and Suppliers</strong><br />\r\n		Our purpose is to sell a wide variety of travel related products from different suppliers and service providers. Each supplier has its own terms and conditions applicable to your particular arrangements in addition to our general terms and conditions, so you should make sure you have understood them well.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		The role of Venacuba is to act as an intermediary or a &quot;Booking Agent&quot; for those products and services not directly supplied by us. We want to make clear that we are not a co-vendor of such products and services. It is important for you to know that you will be entering into a separate contract with such suppliers (HOSTAL or CASA) in relation to those products and services.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Deposits and Payment</strong><br />\r\n		After you provide your payment information, you authorize us to make all the payments to the corresponding suppliers.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Documentation</strong><br />\r\n		Our general policy is to send the documents to our customers by electronic means whenever possible. We reserve the right to charge an administration fee if such documents are requested to be sent as a hard copy.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Cancellations and Changes</strong><br />\r\n		As your booking agent, in case of ANY change we will ensure that you are notified in time if there are significant changes in the trip or stay. However, we do not accept any liability for changes or costs incurred as a result of this. Subject to the terms and conditions stated by the supplier, you will then have the choice of accepting the changes or not. You are free to accept an alternative offer to your trip or decline your booked arrangements and receive the applicable refunds.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Please, it is important to notice that you must make sure you have provided us your contact e-mail address and that you regularly check your messages before leaving.</p>\r\n	<h2>\r\n		<a id=\"h.ffl96zafox80\" name=\"h.ffl96zafox80\"></a>2. The Agreement With Us</h2>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Accepting these Terms and Conditions</strong><br />\r\n		When you book with us or use our website, you agree to be bound to the terms contained in this agreement and to any additional terms and conditions stated by the suppliers which are applicable to your booking, travel arrangements or use of any website content. It is important to be aware that you agree on behalf of yourself and those you represent and have to accede with all such terms and conditions, which include the payment of all the required amounts when due. When accepting these Terms and Conditions you agree that any violation may result in: (a) the invalidation of your reservation or purchase, (b) the incautation of the amount you paid for the reservation or purchase, (c) the denial to the access to the applicable travel related the product or service that has been offered.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		You must take into account that you represent and warrant that (a) you are of legal age so you can use our services and website and at the same time you are capable of complying with the legal obligations related to their use, (b) you are legally authorized to act on behalf of those you represent and accept these terms and conditions on their behalf, and (c) the information you supplied regarding you and your group is real and correct.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		You are responsible for informing the other persons that come with you about all the terms and conditions applicable to the travel arrangements. You accept that you are responsible &ndash; in financial terms - for any use of our services or website by you and those under your name or account.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>What If You Change Your Booking?</strong><br />\r\n		If you decide or need to change your booking we will do our best to help you in any possible way regarding the changes you need in your travel arrangements if possible. Our standard service fees will always apply in addition to any additional supplier charges. It is important for you to take into account that all reservation changes are subject to availability as well as the terms and conditions of the product to be purchased.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>What If You Have A Complaint?</strong><br />\r\n		In case you have any problem during your stay, you have the right to inform the relevant supplier (e.g. the B&amp;B owners) at once. If they are not able to solve the problem, please contact us immediately by using the contact information on our website. Our purpose is to help you solve and clear any dispute or dissatisfaction. But, if you do not contact us in time, it will be more difficult for us to better investigate about your complaint and it will be harder to amend any error while you are away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Travel Documents and Destinations</strong><br />\r\n		Please note that you need to ensure that all the details on your travel documents are real and correct. Please inform us in time in case of errors or discrepancies that may occur. Remember that your travel documents are very important and they should be protected as if they were gold because it is not always possible to replace them in case they are lost, stolen, damaged, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Passport, Visa and Immigration Requirements</strong><br />\r\n		You are responsible for fulfilling your passport, visa and other immigration requirements that could be asked to you during your itinerary. Please confirm all this with the relevant embassies and/or consulates. We are not bound to any responsibility in the case you are unable to travel because you do not comply with such requirements.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Insurance</strong><br />\r\n		When you travel it is important to remember that insurance is a vital part of your arrangements. We recommend you to take the proper insurance for your trip. This is a mandatory element when leaving home. If you need it we can arrange any travel insurance you require. We will send you a quote, and answer to any queries you may have regarding this.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>The Use of our Services and Website</strong><br />\r\n		In this item you agree that you will use our website or services with the only purpose of making legitimate reservations or purchases and not to make speculative, false or fraudulent reservations. You agree to legally use our website and services in compliance with the applicable laws.<br />\r\n		If you do not have our written permission, you are not entitled to (a) access, monitor or copy any content or information on our website, you cannot use any &quot;robot,&quot; &quot;spider,&quot; or other automated or manual device or program for this purpose, (b) deep link to any portion of our website, or (c) &quot;frame&quot; or incorporate any portion of our website into any other website.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Indemnification</strong><br />\r\n		Here you agree to indemnify us and our affiliates, and any of our suppliers, or others related to us such us officers, directors, employees and agents against any claims, causes of action, demands, losses, damages, or other costs, (including reasonable legal and accounting fees) that may be caused by you or third parties under your name as a result of (a) a breach of this Agreement, (b) a violation of any law or rights of any third party, or (c) the use given by you and those under you name to our website.</p>','en'),(7,7,'Contact Us','Contact Us','Contact Us','Contact Us','<ul class=\"contact-info\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<img alt=\"mail\" src=\"/img/images/message.png\" style=\"width: 31px; height: 23px;\" /> <a href=\"mailto:info@mytriptocuba.com\">info@mytriptocuba.com</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<img alt=\"mail\" src=\"/img/images/phone.png\" />1(844)836-2822</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','en'),(8,8,'Hospitality','Hospitality','Hospitality','Hospitality','<p>\r\n	The Cuban people along with the island&acute;s natural sceneries are Cuba&acute;s most valuable treasure.<br />\r\n	This is a country that has built its history and forged its culture and idiosyncrasy based on its talent and and affection. Those are the essential components of the hospitality that distinguish us and this is what our visitors take back home when they leave. When you arrive they receive you by using your first name, as friends are welcomed.<br />\r\n	&ldquo;Come this way&rdquo; &ldquo;This is your room&rdquo;, &ldquo;the kitchen is over there&rdquo;, those are the phrases said by the Cubans and not any other.<br />\r\n	There is no need to say &ldquo;this is your house too&rdquo;, because during those days it is your house indeed.<br />\r\n	For that reason, when needing something, you just have to say: &ldquo;I would like&hellip;&rdquo; those are<br />\r\n	the magic words. <strong><em>They will</em></strong>&nbsp; take you wherever you want and will provide you all that you wish.</p>\r\n','en'),(9,9,'Stories','Stories','Stories','Stories','<p>The stories experienced  by Cuban women and men are an invitation to meet them. They are not only &ldquo;the  lessors that rent a room to you&rdquo; with the proper comforts so that you, your  family and friends enjoy your vacations. They open their houses so the visitors  can feel like being in their own places. But, the most important thing is that  they bridge the gap - with the due respect - of cold distancing and protocols  while offering their more human side to you. </p>','en'),(10,10,'Trust & Safety','Trust & Safety','Trust & Safety','Trust & Safety','<p>\r\n	The island offers security and carelessness in its ample meaning. If you are not yet convinced, please ask your lessor to tell you about the places you should avoid. Please, only trust in the information given by VENACUBA. The representatives will identify you by your name, reservation number and destination. Your Cuban lessor will help you to obtain all the additional services preferred by you.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	When choosing your destination, we always want to select a safe place, especially when we travel with our family. Cuba is a safe place. Public health, no violence due to firearms, drugs, or ethnic conflicts.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It is a society with its typical characters that make it rich from a social and cultural point of view.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	One of the most outstanding characters appeared during the 90s: the &ldquo;Jinetero (a) s&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<strong>What is a Jinetero (a)? </strong>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some words to define a &ldquo;jinetero&rdquo; could be: escort, sexual service, tour guide, a pioneer at the &ldquo;underground&rdquo; life, collector of commissions&hellip; even a great trickster, that and even more, customized services. These are the elements that characterize this subject that - although in a slight way - is part of the adventure of coming to Cuba.</p>\r\n','en'),(11,11,'Recreation','Recreation','Recreation','Recreation','<p>\r\n	recreation pages goes here</p>\r\n','en'),(12,12,'Food & Drinks','Food & Drinks','Food & Drinks','Food & Drinks','<p>Cuban cuisine is indeed the result of a fusion of several cultures including Native American Taino food, Spanish, African, and Caribbean cuisines. You will taste the flavor of the Cuban cuisine prepared with spices and techniques shared with the Spanish and African cooking. You will also discover some Caribbean influence in Cuban spices and flavors. Cuban cuisine turns to be then a unique, interesting and flavorful mixture of those nearby and distance influences including strong similarities with the cuisine of other islander countries like the Dominican Republic and Puerto Rico. The essence of the Cuban uniqueness dates back to colonial times, when the island had important ports for trade, especially Havana, and many Spaniards who lived in the island brought their culinary traditions to the island. Later, a massive arrival of enslaved Africans contributed with more flavors and ways to prepare food.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A Cuban typical food</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It would simply consist of rice and beans, cooked together or apart. If cooked together then the recipe is called \"Congri\", \"Moros\" or \"Moros y Cristianos\", which means black beans and rice. When cooked separately the recipe is called \"Arroz con/y Frijoles\" (rice with/and beans).[3] Then, the typical main course added is usually pork or beef. There are some Cuban recipes like \"Ropa Vieja\" that are prepared with such meats. Something that is usually added to the typical Cuban dish is the vianda (starchy roots and tubers) (do not confuse with the French word viande which means “meat\". The term vianda encompasses several types of tubers, including yuca (manioc), malanga (taro), and papas (potatoes) all served either boiled or fried. A Cuban typical dish cannot miss either plantains or corn. A salad usually accompanies the food and it could be simply composed of tomato, lettuce, avocado, or cucumber. The salad dressing is generally simple, using vinegar or dry wine. A curious fact about criollo foods is that they largely ignore fruit, except for ripe plantains, that are very consumed and appreciated along with rice and beans.</p>\r\n<strong>Some Cuban traditional and common dishes</strong>\r\n<p>Lechón asado (roasted pork)<br>\r\nYuca con mojo (manioc with garlic sauce)<br>\r\nArroz congris (black beans and rice)<br>\r\nChatinos o Tostones (fried unripe plantains)<br>\r\nPicadillo a la criolla (Cuban style creole mince)<br>\r\nCarne con papas (meat and potatoes)<br>\r\nAjiaco (it is a hearty stew made from beef, pork, chicken, vegetables, and a variety of starchy roots and tubers classified as viandas)\r\nCongrí oriental (Cuban red beans and rice) <br>\r\nSándwich cubano (Cuban sandwich)<br>\r\nCaldosa (a Cuban typical broth)<br>\r\nRopa vieja vegetales con carne (Ropa vieja, vegetables and meat)<br>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Drinks</h2>\r\n\r\n<strong>Here is a list containing the most popular Cuban cocktails:</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>Daiquirí: rum, lemon, sugar, maraschino, and ice.<br>\r\nMojito: rum, peppermint leaves, lemon, sugar, soda (sparkling) and ice.<br>\r\nCuba Libre: rum, Coca Cola, lemon and ice.<br>\r\nRon Collins or Rum Colins: rum, lemon, sugar, soda (sparkling) and ice.<br>\r\nTelegrama: rum, mint liquor and ice.</p>\r\n','en'),(13,13,'Technical Support','Technical Support','Technical Support','Technical Support','<p>\r\n	Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry&#39;s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containi